<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ910415-0127</DOCNO><DOCID>910415-0127.</DOCID><HL>   Boeing Team Obtains   An Army Installment</HL><DATE>04/15/91</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE B4</SO><CO>   BA HSC TXT UT</CO><MS>CONGLOMERATES (CGL)INDUSTRIAL (IDU)TECHNOLOGY (TEC)UTILITIES (UTI)</MS><IN>AEROSPACE (ARO)DIVERSIFIED INDUSTRIAL (IDD)</IN><GV>DEFENSE DEPARTMENT (DEF)</GV><RE>MISSOURI (MO)PENNSYLVANIA (PA)RHODE ISLAND (RI)WASHINGTON (WA)</RE><LP>   WASHINGTON -- The Boeing-Sikorsky team received a $241million installment on its contract to develop a new lighthelicopter for the Army.   The venture, led by Boeing Co. and United TechnologiesCorp.'s Sikorsky Aircraft unit, was chosen earlier this monthfor the $2 billion project.                                                                                                       </LP><TEXT>   BMY Combat Systems, a division of Harsco Corp., got a$29.6 million Army contract for tank turrets.                                                                                                          Textron Inc. received an $18.3 million Air Force contractfor aerial weapons. Bell Helicopter Textron Inc., a unit ofTextron, got a $10.8 million Army contract for helicoptertests.                                                                                                          The Aerojet Ordnance unit of Aerojet General Corp.received a $13.9 million Army contract for 30mm ammunition.                                                                                                          ESL Inc. got a $20 million Army contract for airbornereconnaissance systems.</TEXT></DOC>